President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of New Hampshire due to a severe storm and flooding that occurred from July 29 to July 30, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically the counties of Cheshire and Sullivan. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Deanne Criswell, Administrator of FEMA, has appointed William Roy as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Media inquiries can be directed to the FEMA News Desk.